3:
The earth will be completely devastated and completely stripped;
\q1 for Yahweh has spoken this word.
\q1

8:
The happy sound of the tambourines stops, and the revelry of those who rejoice;
\q1 the joy of the lyre ceases.
\q1

16:
From the farthest part of the earth we have heard songs, "Glory to the righteous one!"
\q1 But I said, "I have wasted away, I have wasted away, woe is me! The treacherous have dealt treacherously;
\q1 yes, the treacherous have dealt very treacherously."

19:
The earth will be completely broken, the earth ripped apart;
\q1 the earth will be violently shaken.
\q1

22:
They will be gathered together, prisoners in a pit, and will be shut up in a prison;
\q1 and after many days they will be punished.
\q1
